[
  "Joe Mansueto started independent investment research firm, Morningstar, in 1984 with $80,000 in savings.",
  " In January 2017 Mansueto stepped down as CEO after more than 30 years at the helm.",
  "He owns approximately 49% of the publicly traded firm, which manages or advises on over $200 billion in assets.",
  "In 2018, the Chicagoan paid $255 million for the iconic Wrigley Building and $106 million to buy Belden-Stratford apartments.",
  "Mansueto bought a 49% stake in soccer team Chicago Fire in summer 2018, taking full ownership in September 2019."
]